summaries.short: Season Two Premiere. Jonathan is hired by a cop with an S&M fetish; George is told to make do with less; Ray fails a yoga test.
summaries.full: Season Two Premiere. Taking time out from his new gig as a night-school creative-writing teacher, Jonathan is hired by a cop to infiltrate an S&M dungeon where his name is on their client list. Meanwhile, George is flummoxed to learn that his new publisher plans to cut costs on every front, and Ray fails a yoga test with Leah, putting their relationship in final jeopardy.

summaries.full: Jonathan is hired by Richard Antrem, George's nemesis and boxing foe, to investigate Richard's suspicions that his wife Priscilla (George's ex) is having an affair. Jonathan's insecurities resurface when Stella announces she's not over her first love. George learns he has a new female urologist; Ray plots to win back Leah by penning a comic book.

summaries.short: In the Season One finale, George, Jonathan and Ray step into the ring for a grudge match against their publishing rivals.
summaries.full: Season One finale. Having picked up the gauntlet thrown by Richard--and having thwarted a blackmail bid aimed at getting Jonathan to take a dive--George, Jonathan and Ray gear up for a boxing challenge against their GQ rivals. But with the bouts only hours away, the women in their lives offer up some compelling reasons why winning a fight isn't everything.

summaries.full: Jonathan is enlisted to retrieve a sex tape that a female escort is using to extort money from a married New Jersey man. With Ray and George in tow, Jonathan ends up in a motel room with the escort, who attempts to blackmail him as well. Can the very stoned Ray and George save Jonathan's neck before the woman's enraged brother breaks it?
